  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_4' aria-label=\" K. Valarmathi & Ors. versus Kumaresan pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('4','2025','2025_4_2461_2466','2025INSC606'); ><font size='4'> <strong>K. VALARMATHI & ORS.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>KUMARESAN </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 4 S.C.R. 2461</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 606</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007042025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PAMIDIGHANTAM SRI NARASIMHA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, JOYMALYA BAGCHI</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Can the High Court in exercise of its supervisory jurisdiction under Article 227 reject a plaint. Headnotes&dagger; Constitution of India &ndash; Art.227 &ndash; Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 &ndash; Supervisory jurisdiction &ndash; Rejection of plaint by the High Court of the power under Article 227 being supervisory, it cannot be invoked to usurp the original jurisdiction of the court which it seeks to supervise &ndash; Nor can it be invoked to supplant a statutory legal remedy under the Civil Procedure Code, 1908 &ndash; Civil Procedure Code is a<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 29-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 5677/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('4','2025','2025_4_2461_2466','2025INSC606','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' cl